<h2>Using Cassette in MVC</h2>
<p>
The Cassette <code>Assets</code> helper class is in the <code>Cassette.UI</code> namespace.
The nuget package updates the <code>~\Views\Web.config</code> to make this namespace available in view pages.
</p>
<p>Note: If you are using MVC Areas, then you need to edit the <code>Web.config</code> for each area in a similar manner.</p>
<pre><code><span class="open-tag">&lt;</span><span class="tag">configuration</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
    ...
    <span class="open-tag">&lt;</span><span class="tag">system.web.webPages.razor</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
        <span class="open-tag">&lt;</span><span class="tag">pages</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
            <span class="open-tag">&lt;</span><span class="tag">namespaces</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
                ...
                <strong><span class="open-tag">&lt;</span><span class="tag">add</span> <span class="attribute">namespace</span><span class="attribute-value">="Cassette.UI"</span><span class="close-tag">/&gt;</span></strong>
            <span class="open-tag">&lt;/</span><span class="tag">namespaces</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
        <span class="open-tag">&lt;/</span><span class="tag">pages</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
    <span class="open-tag">&lt;/</span><span class="tag">system.web.webPages.razor</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
    ...
<span class="open-tag">&lt;/</span><span class="tag">configuration</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
</code></pre>

<h3>Cassette in Razor views</h3>
<p>Use code blocks to define references. Use inline expressions for the render calls.</p>
<pre><code><span class="code-tag">@@{</span>
    <span class="code-type">Assets</span>.Scripts.Reference(<span class="string">"scripts/lib/jquery.js"</span>);
    <span class="code-type">Assets</span>.Scripts.Reference(<span class="string">"scripts/app/home.js"</span>);
<span class="code-tag">}</span>
<span class="open-tag">&lt;!</span><span class="tag">DOCTYPE</span> <span class="attribute">html</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
<span class="open-tag">&lt;</span><span class="tag">html</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
<span class="open-tag">&lt;</span><span class="tag">head</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
    <span class="open-tag">&lt;</span><span class="tag">title</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>Web App<span class="open-tag">&lt;/</span><span class="tag">title</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
    <span class="code-tag">@@</span><span class="razor-expression"><span class="code-type">Assets</span>.Stylesheets.Render()</span>
<span class="open-tag">&lt;/</span><span class="tag">head</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
<span class="open-tag">&lt;</span><span class="tag">body</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
    ...
    <span class="code-tag">@@</span><span class="razor-expression"><span class="code-type">Assets</span>.Scripts.Render()</span>
<span class="open-tag">&lt;/</span><span class="tag">body</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span>
<span class="open-tag">&lt;/</span><span class="tag">html</span><span class="close-tag">&gt;</span></code></pre>

